{"parse":{"title":"child","pageid":4487,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Child|Child.}}\n==English==\n[[File:MDRBobMomSmall.jpg|right|thumb|A woman with two children [[circa|c.]] 1933.]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈt͡ʃaɪ̯ld/|[ˈt͡ʃʰaɪ̯ld]}}\n** {{audio|en|en-uk-child.ogg|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-child.ogg|a=GA}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈt͡ʃɑɪ̯ld/|[ˈt͡ʃʰɑ̟ɪ̯ld]|;|/ˈt͡ʃɒ̈ɪ̯ld/|[ˈt͡ʃɒ̈ɪ̯ld]|a=AU,NZ}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈt͡ʃaːld/|[ˈt͡ʃʰaːld]|a=Southern US,ZA,[[w:Monophthongization|/aɪ̯/-ungliding]]}}\n* {{rhymes|en|aɪld|s=1}}\n* {{hyph|en|child}}\n* {{hmp|en|childe}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|child}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ċild}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*kilþ}}, {{m|gmw-pro|*kelþ}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*kelþaz||[[womb]]; [[fetus]]}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ǵelt-||[[womb]]}}, perhaps from {{der|en|ine-pro|*gel-||to ball up, amass}}.\n\nCognate with {{cog|da|kuld||[[brood]], [[litter]]}}, {{cog|sv|kull||[[brood]], [[litter]]}}, {{cog|is|kelta}}, {{m|is|kjalta||[[lap]]}}, {{cog|got|𐌺𐌹𐌻𐌸𐌴𐌹||[[womb]]}}, {{cog|sa|जर्त}}, {{m|sa|जर्तु||tr=jártu|[[vulva]]}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|en|childe||archaic}}\n* {{alter|en|chile||eye dialect|Southern US}}\n* {{sense|plural}} {{alter|en|childrens||intentionally incorrect|nonstandard}}; {{alter|en|childs||nonstandard|rare}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|children|childer<l:dialectal,or,archaic>}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|kid aged 0 to 17 years}} {{lb|en|[[Appendix:Glossary#broadly|broadly]]}} A [[person]] who has not yet reached [[adulthood]], whether [[natural]] ([[puberty]]), [[cultural]] ([[initiation]]), or [[legal]] ([[majority]]).\n#: {{syn|en|kid}}\n#: {{hypo|en|newborn|neonate|preteen|adolescent|tweenager|teenager|tween|teen|preadult}}\n#: {{ux|en|Go easy on him: he is but a '''child'''.}}\n#* '''2003''' Powerpuff Girls: 'Twas the Fight Before Christmas (narration)\n#*: {{quote|en|And not just the '''children''', teenagers too. Chuck wants a football, Kathleen a tattoo.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-06-07|author=w:Joseph Stiglitz|volume=188|issue=26|page=19|magazine=w:The Guardian Weekly|title=Globalisation is about taxes too|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2013/may/27/globalisation-is-about-taxes-too|passage=It is time the international community faced the reality: we have an unmanageable, unfair, distortionary global tax regime. {{...}} It is the starving of the public sector which has been pivotal in America no longer being the land of opportunity – with a '''child''''s life prospects more dependent on the income and education of its parents than in other advanced countries.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Dakin Andone|title=3 children who are US citizens — including one with cancer — deported with their mothers, lawyers and advocacy groups say|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.cnn.com/2025/04/27/us/children-us-citizens-deported-honduras/index.html|date=2025-04-27|passage=In one case, a mother was deported and took her 2-year-old '''child''' with her, while the other involves another mother deported and her 4- and 7-year-old '''children''' went with her, the American Civil Liberties Union and the National Immigration Project, among other organizations, said in a news release Friday.}}\n## {{senseid|en|kid aged 1 to 11 years}} {{lb|en|[[pediatrics]]|sometimes, in a [[Appendix:Glossary#strict|stricter]] sense}} A youth aged 1 to 9 years, whereas [[neonate#Noun|neonates]] are aged 0 to 1 month, [[infant#Noun|infants]] are aged 1 to 12 months, and [[adolescent#Noun|adolescents]] are aged 10 to 20 years.\n##: {{hyper|en|kid}}\n##: {{cot|en|newborn|neonate|infant|adolescent|teenager|teen|boy|girl}}\n#: {{ux|en|Regular chores can be appropriate for '''children''', given age-appropriate limits on difficulty level and time on task.}}\n# {{senseid|en|offspring of any age including adulthood}} {{lb|en|with possessive}} One's [[direct]] [[descendant]] by [[birth]], regardless of [[age]]; one's [[offspring]]; a [[son]] or [[daughter]].\n#: {{ux|en|My youngest '''child''' is forty-three this year.}}\n#: {{ux|en|His adult '''children''' visit him yearly.}}\n# {{senseid|en|cartomancy}} {{lb|en|cartomancy}} The thirteenth [[Lenormand]] card.\n# {{senseid|en|figuratively, of times or tribes}} {{lb|en|figurative}} A [[figurative]] [[offspring]], ''particularly:''\n## A person considered a [[product]] of a [[place]] or [[culture]], a [[member]] of a [[tribe]] or culture, regardless of age.\n##: {{ux|en|the '''children''' of Israel}}\n##: {{ux|en|He is a '''child''' of his times.}}\n##* {{quote-book|en|year=1984|author=[[w:Mary Jane Phillips-Matz|Mary Jane Matz]]|title=The Many Lives of Otto Kahn: A Biography|page=5|passage=For more than forty years, he preached the creed of art and beauty. He was heir to the ancient wisdom of Israel, a '''child''' of Germany, a subject of Great Britain, later an American citizen, but in truth a citizen of the world.}}\n##* {{quote-book|en|year=2009|author=[[w:Edward Plunkett, 18th Baron of Dunsany|Edward John Moreton Dunsany]]|title={{w|The Last Book of Wonder|Tales of Wonder}}|page=64|passage=Plash-Goo was of the '''children''' of the giants, whose sire was Uph. And the lineage of Uph had dwindled in bulk for the last five hundred years, till the giants were now no more than fifteen foot high; but Uph ate elephants{{...}}}}\n## {{senseid|en|figuratively, derived or caused}} Anything [[derive]]d from or [[cause]]d by something.\n##* {{quote-book|en|year=1991|author=w:Salman Rushdie| title={{w|Midnight's Children|Midnight's '''Children'''}}| passage=Poverty, disease, and despair are the '''children''' of war.}}\n## {{senseid|en|child element in computing}} {{lb|en|computing}} A [[data]] [[item]], [[process]], or [[object]] which has a [[subservient]] or [[derivative]] [[role]] relative to another.\n##: {{ux|en|The '''child''' node then stores the actual data of the parent node.}}\n##* {{quote-text|en|year=2011|author=John Mongan; Noah Kindler; Eric Giguère|title=Programming Interviews Exposed\n|passage=The algorithm pops the stack to obtain a new current node when there are no more '''children''' (when it reaches a leaf).}}\n# {{senseid|en|childe, youth of noble birth}} {{alt form|en|childe||youth of noble birth}}.\n# {{senseid|en|mathematics}} {{lb|en|mathematics|programming}} A subordinate [[node]] of a [[tree]].\n# {{lb|en|figurative}} An adult or adolescent with [[childish]] or [[stupid]] behaviors.\n#:{{usex|en|My husband is such a '''child''', going out with his sled everytime it snows.}}\n# {{senseid|en|female child, obsoletely}} {{lb|en|obsolete|specifically}} A [[female]] child, a [[girl]].\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Winter's Tale|III|iii|288|2|passage=A boy, or a '''Childe''' I wonder?}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{sense|young person}} ''See'' '''[[Thesaurus:child]]''', '''[[Thesaurus:boy]]''', and '''[[Thesaurus:girl]]'''\n* {{sense|offspring}} ''See'' '''[[offspring]]''' and '''[[Thesaurus:son]]''' and '''[[Thesaurus:daughter]]''', {{l|en|binary clone}}, {{l|en|progeny}}, {{l|en|hybrid}}\n* {{sense|descendant}} ''See'' '''[[descendant]]'''\n* {{sense|product of a place or era}} {{l|en|product}}, {{l|en|son}} {{qualifier|male}}, [[daughter]] {{qualifier|female}}\n\n=====Antonyms=====\n* {{antsense|offspring}} {{l|en|father}}, {{l|en|mother}}, {{l|en|parent}}\n* {{antsense|person below the age of adulthood}} {{l|en|adult}}\n* {{antsense|data item, process or object in a subordinate role}} {{l|en|parent}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en\n|a burnt child dreads the fire\n|abandoned child syndrome\n|adult child\n|antichild\n|barrel child\n|battered child syndrome\n|belchild\n|biochild|spirit child\n|birthchild\n|black child\n|boomerang child\n|boychild\n|brainchild\n|butterfly child\n|call someone everything but a child of God\n|Chester\n|child abuse\n|child abuser\n|child actor\n|child benefit\n|child birth,child-birth,childbirth\n|child bride,child-bride\n|child car seat\n|child care,childcare\n|child carrier\n|child category\n|child diddler\n|child endangerment\n|child groom\n|child labor,child labour\n|child language\n|child lifter\n|child lock\n|child minder,childminder\n|child molestation\n|child molester\n|child neglect\n|child node\n|child of the kitchen\n|child of the manse\n|child porn\n|child pornography\n|child prodigy\n|child prostitution\n|child restraint\n|child safety seat\n|child seat\n|child sex abuse\n|child sex crime\n|child sex tourism\n|child sexual abuse\n|child sexual abuse material\n|child soldier\n|child support\n|child toucher,child-toucher\n|child trafficking\n|child's play\n|child-bearing,childbearing\n|child-bed,childbed \n|child-centered\n|child-crowing\n|child-directed speech\n|child-free\n|child-fucker,childfucker\n|child-great\n|child-in-law\n|child-like,childlike\n|child-mind,childmind\n|child-nature\n|child-rearing,childrearing\n|childbearer\n|childcarer\n|childcaring\n|childhood\n|childie\n|childification\n|childish\n|childism\n|childkind\n|childless\n|childline\n|childling\n|childlore\n|childlove\n|childlover\n|childness\n|childproof\n|childraiser\n|childraising\n|childrearer\n|childsafe\n|childship\n|childspeak\n|childtime\n|childwear\n|choirchild\n|chomo\n|chrisom child\n|cowchild\n|dog-child\n|dreamchild\n|elf-child\n|feral child\n|flower child\n|foster child\n|get with child\n|girlchild\n|glass child\n|god-child,godchild \n|golden child\n|grandchild,grand-child\n|heavy with child\n|home child\n|honey child,honey chile\n|Indigo child\n|inner child\n|innocent as the child unborn\n|International Day of the Girl Child\n|iPad child\n|it is a wise child that knows his own father\n|it takes a village to raise a child\n|latch-key child,latchkey child\n|lovechild,love-child,love child\n|maid child,maid-child\n|man child,man-child,manchild\n|merchild\n|middle child\n|minor child\n|moonchild\n|natural child\n|nonchild\n|once a man, twice a child\n|once a woman, twice a child\n|one-child policy\n|only child\n|password child\n|poster child\n|pretermitted child\n|problem child\n|saleschild\n|schoolch